} \\approx 10^{11}\\, {\\rm M}_{\\odot}$)\nsatellites, respectively. SF fades in $\\approx 1.5\\,{\\rm Gyr}$, largely\nindependent of stellar mass. We find that the SF quenching of low-mass\nsatellites supports the so-called delay-then-rapid quenching scenario. However,\nthe SF history of $z=0$ passive satellites of any stellar mass is better\ndescribed by a delay-then-fade quenching scenario.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Jan 2018 17:22:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Oct 2018 20:29:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-12-05"}
