d, $\\gamma^+>0$, the entire network splits into a\nset of weakly connected clusters, while below another threshold, $\\gamma^-<0$,\nthe network acquires a bipartite graph structure. Our results propose\nmechanisms of formation of self-organized communities in international\ncommunication between countries, as well as in crime clans and prehistoric\nsocieties.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Jan 2018 18:26:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 30 Mar 2018 13:22:26 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 13 Aug 2018 18:57:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-26"}
