 this work, we inspect trends between $\\text{f}_\\text{shocked}$ and\ndynamical encounter parameters. Our findings are generally consistent with\nshocks being produced either by the direct collision of the ISM or by the chain\nof events provoked by the tidal impulse during the first passage.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 11 Jan 2018 20:34:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 30 May 2019 20:06:17 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-05"}
